[SN]TITLE[SN]
Thieves steal bags worth £30,000 from Edinburgh shop

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Dozens of bags worth up to £30,000 have been stolen from a shop in Edinburgh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Thieves broke into Handbag Heaven in Howe Street at about 02:15 on Friday and stole 85 bags, worth between £20,000 and £30,000.
Police said officers arrived at the scene within a minute but the thieves, understood to be three men, had already left the scene.
They drove off in a small silver-coloured vehicle. Police have appealed for witnesses to contact them.
